In the treatment of Russian authors one will often (or maybe not so often) come across the word ''kalembur''. It means pun - and especially [[Nikolai Gogol]] is known for his extensive use of kalemburs in his texts. The russian [[formalist]] Boris Ejchenbaum wrote an aticle about Gogol's short story "The Coat" in which he treats Gogols estensive use of kalemburs in his text.

See also: [[Russian formalism]].

